                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Tall rectangular stone slab in almost perfect condition, with a carved entablature in centre for receiving text. Carved entabulature is smooth, but other surfaces slightly abraded. All sides are complete, the top edge has been slightly rounded. No autopsy of sides, top or back.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">Marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/250.html">Stele</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">118</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">45</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">16</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.complete"/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>
                                    <p>The text is roughly centred at the top of the entablature. The text takes up the top third of the carved entabulature, with nothing beneath.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>The text is complete and fully legible. The letter "I" in Primus in line 4 is tall, all other letter heights are roughly equal. The letters are broad, well formed, and well spaced. All letters have neat serifs. The interpuncts are triangular.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line4">Lines 1–4</locus>
